  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, thanks for the app. It is great and easy to use.\r\n\r\nAfter I read some articles, including the ones below, I think I understand a little better how a mnemonic phrase works.\r\n\r\nHowever, I think  that the explanation attached to the question mark symbol next to \"Passphrase (optional):\" in the \"View & Send\" menu is confusing or maybe even misleading.\r\n\r\nIt says \"If you did not setup this additional password when your seed phrase was generated, you do not need to enter anything into this field.\" However, during my process to create a new wallet using a mnemonic phrase, I never got the chance to setup a password.\r\n\r\nIn addition to this and, if I'm not wrong, it is the combination of a mnemonic phrase and a password (or the absence of it), that will provide a list of available addresses to operate with.\r\n\r\nTherefore, the same user could be operating with several accounts generated with the same mnemonic phrase, some with a password, some without them.\r\n\r\nI might be completely wrong about this, as I am still learning about it.\r\n\r\n- https://support.mycrypto.com/general-knowledge/ethereum-blockchain/difference-between-wallet-types\r\n- https://support.mycrypto.com/general-knowledge/cryptography/how-do-mnemonic-phrases-work\r\n\r\nThanks for your time,\r\n",
