    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Thank you for the feedback! You're right that the help description is slighlty misleading in that you don't enter a passphrase during the creation of a new mnemonic phrase. We are working on a replacement for the current desktop application, and this is definitely something we'll keep in mind.\r\n\r\n> In addition to this and, if I'm not wrong, it is the combination of a mnemonic phrase and a password (or the absence of it), that will provide a list of available addresses to operate with.\r\n> \r\n> Therefore, the same user could be operating with several accounts generated with the same mnemonic phrase, some with a password, some without them.\r\n\r\nYep! Private keys are derived (\"generated\") from the mnemonic phrase based on the mnemonic words and optional passphrase. There is no \"wrong\" passphrase here, using a different one will simply result in other private keys (and thus addresses) being derived.\r\n\r\nIf you're interested in learning more about how mnemonic phrases work in-depth, please check [this article](https://medium.com/mycrypto/the-journey-from-mnemonic-phrase-to-address-6c5e86e11e14).",
